            "commit": "5f10f164aceae33dd9a6d4cb3470b6a4874734df",
            "subject": "LU-8661 libcfs: handle padata_alloc() rename"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Steve Guminski",
          "email": "stephenx.guminski@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-14 19:16:23.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-06-13 16:55:53.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 initializers in lfs_setdirstripe()",
        "message": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 initializers in lfs_setdirstripe()\n\nThis patch makes no functional changes.  Struct initializers that\nuse C89 or GCC-only syntax are updated to C99 syntax.\n\nC89 positional initializers require values to be placed in the\ncorrect order. This will cause errors if the fields of the struct\ndefinition are reordered or fields are added or removed. C99 named\ninitializers avoid this problem, and also automatically clear any\nvalues that are not explicitly set.\n\nThis patch updates lfs_setdirstripe() to use the C99 syntax.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I0335cae79bc5f57da3d73b40c17e83f87853ef5f\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/27515\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
